    slug: "sharah-al-aqeeda-al-wastiah",
    description: `Sharah Al Aqeeda Al Wastiah is a scholarly Islamic book that provides a detailed commentary and explanation of Al-Aqeedah Al-Wasitiyyah, one of the most important and widely studied works on Islamic creed (aqeedah) written by the eminent scholar Shaykh al-Islam Ibn Taymiyyah. The original text of Al-Wasitiyyah is a concise yet comprehensive treatise that systematically outlines the beliefs of Ahl al-Sunnah wal-Jama'ah — the mainstream orthodox position in Islamic theology — covering the fundamental articles of faith including belief in Allah, His names and attributes, the angels, the revealed books, the prophets, the Day of Judgment, and the divine decree (qadar). This sharah (commentary) unpacks the dense theological content of the original text, making it accessible to students and scholars who wish to understand the nuances of Islamic creed.

The commentary follows the structure of the original treatise, beginning with the foundational principle of Tawheed — the oneness of Allah — and explaining the three categories of monotheism: Tawheed al-Rububiyyah (Lordship), Tawheed al-Uluhiyyah (Worship), and Tawheed al-Asma wa al-Sifat (Names and Attributes). The author carefully navigates the complex theological debates surrounding the names and attributes of Allah, explaining the balanced approach of the righteous predecessors (salaf al-salih) who affirmed Allah's attributes without likening them to creation (tashbih) and without denying them (ta'til). The commentary addresses the deviations of various sectarian groups that went to extremes in matters of creed, providing rational and textual evidence for the orthodox position from the Quran, the authentic Sunnah, and the consensus of the early scholars.

The book covers the belief in angels and their various roles, including Jibril, Mika'il, Israfil, and the angel of death, along with a discussion of the jinn and their nature. The section on revealed books addresses the original scriptures given to various prophets, the corruption of earlier texts, and the preserved nature of the Quran. The belief in prophets is explored with emphasis on the finality of Prophet Muhammad's prophethood and the requirement to believe in all prophets without discrimination. The chapters on the Day of Judgment provide a detailed account of the events of the Hereafter, including the blowing of the trumpet, the resurrection, the reckoning, the scales, the bridge (sirat), and the intercession. The final section on divine decree addresses the relationship between Allah's knowledge, will, power, and creation, and how human beings have free will within the framework of Allah's predestination. Sharah Al Aqeeda Al Wastiah is an essential resource for students of Islamic theology and anyone seeking a clear, well-documented exposition of orthodox Islamic creed.`,
    metaDescription: "Sharah Al Aqeeda Al Wastiah is a detailed commentary on Ibn Taymiyyah's creed treatise covering Tawheed, angels, prophets, and the Hereafter."
