    slug: "signs-of-the-hour",
    description: `Signs of the Hour is an English-language Islamic book that provides a comprehensive treatment of the signs heralding the approach of the Day of Judgment (Yawm al-Qiyamah) as described in the Quran and the authenticated hadith narrations. The book systematically organizes and explains the various signs that Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) foretold, providing readers with a thorough understanding of this important aspect of Islamic eschatology. The work draws exclusively from authentic sources, carefully distinguishing between well-established narrations and those of lesser reliability, and presents the material in a clear, analytical manner that is accessible to English-speaking readers.

The book begins by establishing the Islamic belief in the Day of Judgment as one of the six articles of faith, explaining why knowledge of its signs matters for a Muslim's spiritual life. The author then divides the signs into their established categories: the minor signs (al-ashrat al-sughra) and the major signs (al-ashrat al-kubra). The minor signs — which the Prophet described as numerous and unfolding gradually — include the passing of the prophets, the conquest of Jerusalem, the spread of wealth, the prevalence of trials and tribulations, the emergence of false prophets, the lifting of knowledge and the prevalence of ignorance, the increased consumption of alcohol and usury, the construction of tall buildings by former desert dwellers, and many other social, moral, and natural phenomena. Each sign is discussed with reference to the specific hadith narrations that mention it, along with scholarly commentary that explains its significance and relevance.

The major signs receive extensive treatment as the dramatic, unmistakable events that will mark the final phase before the Day of Judgment. The book covers the ten major signs in detail: the appearance of the Dajjal (the False Messiah), the descent of Isa ibn Maryam (Jesus, peace be upon him), the emergence of Yajuj and Majuj (Gog and Magog), the sinking of the earth in three places, the appearance of the beast of the earth, the sun rising from the west, the smoke, and the blowing of the trumpet. Each major sign is described with all the authentic narrations pertaining to it, and the author provides scholarly analysis of its nature, timing, and implications. The book also addresses contemporary claims about the appearance of various signs, helping readers distinguish between baseless speculation and established prophetic guidance. Signs of the Hour serves as a reliable reference for anyone seeking an authentic and well-organized treatment of Islamic eschatology.`,
    metaDescription: "Signs of the Hour is an English book detailing the minor and major signs of the Day of Judgment from authentic Quranic and hadith sources."
